# Bootstrap secrets for `just bootstrap`. Copy to `.env` (gitignored) and fill in. `just` auto-loads
# it, so you never `export` these by hand. Non-secret values (account/zone IDs, hostname) do NOT go
# here — those live in infra/terraform.tfvars. Nothing here is committed.

# --- Cloudflare ---
# A general Cloudflare API token (NOT the R2 S3 token below). An Account-owned token (cfat_) or a
# User token (cfut_) both work. Permissions needed:
#   Account > Workers R2 Storage (Edit)          — create the bucket
#   Account > Cloudflare Tunnel (Edit)           — create the tunnel + ingress
#   Account > Access: Apps and Policies (Edit)   — the Access app + allowlist (or Zero Trust Edit)
#   Account > API Tokens (Edit)                  — mint the Litestream R2 token
#   Zone    > DNS (Edit), scoped to your domain  — create the hostname's record (NOT "DNS Settings")
# Paste the whole value, prefix included (older tokens are unprefixed).
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=

# --- GitHub ---
# A PAT with repo scope (fine-grained: Secrets read/write on r4stered/fishpage). Starts with ghp_.
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# --- Grafana Cloud ---
# grafana.com -> Account -> Access Policies: a token with accesspolicies:read|write + stacks:read.
# Starts with glc_.
GRAFANA_CLOUD_ACCESS_POLICY_TOKEN=
# Your <stack>.grafana.net -> Administration -> Service accounts -> add a token (Admin role).
# Starts with glsa_.
GRAFANA_AUTH=

# --- R2 remote-state bucket (S3 API keys) ---
# A separate R2 API token: Cloudflare dashboard -> R2 -> Manage R2 API Tokens -> Create (with
# read/write to the fishpage-tfstate bucket). It returns an Access Key ID (~32 hex), a Secret Access
# Key (~64 hex), and an S3 endpoint. The keys go here; the S3 endpoint goes in infra/backend.hcl.
# These authenticate the encrypted remote-state backend, nothing else.
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=

# --- Fly ---
# A deploy token for CD only — it becomes the FLY_API_TOKEN GitHub Actions secret. Paste the output
# of:  fly tokens create deploy -a fishpage   (starts with "FlyV1 ").
TF_VAR_fly_deploy_token=
#
# Do NOT set FLY_API_TOKEN here. A deploy token cannot create the app, and an empty value would
# override your CLI session. Authenticate flyctl for bootstrap with `fly auth login` instead.

# --- Anthropic ---
# The API key the enricher calls Claude with. Becomes the ANTHROPIC_API_KEY Fly secret; paired with
# ENRICHMENT_ENABLED (fly.toml) it switches the AI care classifiers on. Mint at console.anthropic.com
# -> Settings -> API Keys. Starts with "sk-ant-".
TF_VAR_anthropic_api_key=

# --- OpenTofu state encryption ---
# A passphrase you choose, >= 16 chars. It derives the key that encrypts remote state (which holds
# the minted secrets). Guard it like the secrets themselves — losing it locks you out of state.
TF_VAR_state_encryption_passphrase=
